# Edito #
#########

@Node Edito "Editorial"

Heads up !
 
Yeah man !!! Here  is  the  fourth issue  of your favourite magazine.
I am happy, Point & Rock is well  spread  through  the World with the
help of Internet and IRC. I post every new edition on Aminet and some
friends of mine ( Lestat... ) give it where they can ! 

I begin to have some response from everywhere : a  belgian  guy wrote
me today  to contribute ( well  done  mate, I  will  use  your  cover
picture, some lyrics and of course your votes ). Good news for me, he
was pleased to read me ! It  seems  that  such  kind  of magazine was
missing so be sure that I'll keep my way !

I have also joined a new group on Amiga... It's a polish group called
Stage Diving Club, group  where  members  listen  only  to Hard Rock.
I would like to take the occasion to officialy thank them for joining
me. I hope  there  will  be  a good  cooperation  between us. Special
greets to my contacts in this group : Korball, Blaze and FlapJack.

In this issue, we  unfortunately  have  any  concert report. There is
no great shows around  here  for  the  moment, but  I count on you to
supply it to me ( I don't care if it was  on  the  other  side of the
planet :) ).

This month will see the birth of many new albums : we  are waiting of
Nine  Lives ( @{"Aerosmith" Link Aero_info} - see  the  test in  this  issue ), The More
Things Change ( Machine Head ), Remanufacture ( Fear Factory ) and so
on, so  stay  tuned  'till  the next  edition  for  more  information
( and maybe tests of these albums ).

It's also the second time that we have to  announce you a split. Last
issue it was Guns n' Roses, this time it's Sepultura !!! Read more in
our @{"article" Link article}.

That's it, I wish you a nice reading, keep on rocking man !





                                         Raphaël ^ Mister No/aßS

@Endnode

###########
# Article #
###########

@Node Article "Sepultura A.D. -- The end of an era ???"

@{b}Sepultura A.D. -- The end of an era ???@{ub}

@{"Picture of Sepultura 1" Link Sys:Images/Sepultura_4.jpg/MAIN}
@{"Picture of Sepultura 2" Link Sys:Images/Sepultura2_4.jpg/MAIN}

Some  days  ago,  a  friend of mine told  me this terrible news : Max
Cavalera has decided to leave the band ! I couldn't  believe it until
I read in  the  press  that  it was  true. In a previous article in a
magazine, Max told that if a member  of  Sepultura  decided to leave,
band would @{b}NEVER@{ub} be the same. Some  weeks later, himself left for the
following reasons.

Will @{"Roots" Link Sys:Images/Roots_4.jpg/Main} be the last album of Sepultura with Max ???

You probably know that Max is married to Gloria Cavalera  and she was
until now the manager of Sepultura. For some reasons explained later,
Paulo Jr, Andreas Kisser and Igor Cavalera ( the three other  members
of the band ) decided to fire their manager. It  seems that they were
bored that Gloria managed more Max than the rest of the group. It was
always Max Cavalera on the magazines' covers...

Gloria  said in an interview : " The reasons ( P/A/I fired her ) were
cause the're jealous of Max   and because  of their  greed. They said
Max was becoming too famous, and myself was  becoming  too famous and
that my children were becoming famous too. They  also  got pissed off
when I quit  the  europeean  tour after my son  died. They never said
confort words when Dana died. That has left me schocked."

We have also read that Paulo, Igor and Andreas were complaining about
that Gloria was taking more money that she deserved.
The answer of Gloria : "Shortly after our last concert, on  December,
Andreas said said I was a great manager and  that he knew I never had
touched on any money that did not belong to me. But there's been lots
of insinuation, specially by I/P/A's wives."

On the other side, some say that there was a lot  of  tension  in the
band and that  could  explain  the  reason of the split. But the more
given reason is the replacement of Gloria.

In the future, Max said that he will continue a solo carrier ( and he
will be managed by  Oasis  Management, which is... Gloria Cavalera ).
He would like to work with his brother Igor, but  he  doesn't want to
hear about Paulo and Andreas. Max is planning  to  continue to create
weird and strong music as he was doing in Sepultura and even more !!!
He feels now free to compose what he want.

The three other members will  continue  their  work under the name of
Sepultura. The new vocalist of the band will be Andreas and they keep
their Roadrunner Label.

So, that's it ! It seems that divorce is complete. It's  a shame that
this happened because, in  my humble opinion, Sepultura was rising to
a great destiny. I wait now more informations about that subject.

If you want  to  learn  more  about  that, I suggest you to visit the
following internet site ( where I get  the stuff for this article ) :

http://www.geocities.com/sunsetstrip/6666/s_split.html
http://www.lut.fi/~moro/sepu.html

@endnode

@Node Downset "Downset : 1 out of 3 women will be raped in her lifetime"

@{b}"1 out of 3 women will be raped in her lifetime.
  
                                    STOP SEXUAL VIOLENCE NOW !!"@{ub}


That's  what  you  can read when you open the CD box and when you put
off the donwset CD of  its place. This time, no more noisy pop-music,
now it's time to rise your fist and to protest......

Donwset is, as the name doesn't tell it, a fusion group. When you put
one of these CD's  in your  cd-player, you  can  feel the temperature
rising and  the atmosphere  becoming more  and more palpable. L.A. is
near, you  can  hear  the  sirens  screaming  all through the Central
Banking  District  and  suddenly  it  starts,  the  cool  speedy  and
aggressive lyrics of Ray takes control of your brain, and at the same
time, a really cool music strikes your ears. The anger is growing and
this time for a good reason....

The first  album  seems  to  be in the same style than the well known
Rage Against The Machine but in a more aggressive form and style. The
second one explores more different styles of music, always fusion but
punk too.

The  coolest tracks ( there are nothing bad on  these two albums, the
whole thing is delicious ) are "ANGER", "RITUAL", "BREED THE KILLER",
"SICKNESS", "AGAINST THE SPIRITS", "ENPOWER", and in the intro on the
second CD, you can hear M. Luther  King during a speech, during "THE"
speech about the well world-wide-known :


                         "I have a dream"

simply cool.

As  always  in  the  fusion style, the U.S. system explodes under the
hits of the lyrics, and bullets of sound.... tasty !!

The members of this pack are for the 1st album ( simply "Downset" ) :

                   -Ray Anthony Oropeza as singer
                   -Rogelio Lozano as guitar
                   -James Morris as bass
                   -Chris lee as drums
                   -Ares as guitar

                    
and for  the  second album ( "Do We Speak A Dead Language" ) the band
is now :
                    
                   -Ray Anthony Oropeza always as singer
                   -James Morris still on the bass
                   -Chris lee hits his drums like ever
                   -Ares shoot you down one more time with his guitar

Rogelio Lozano seems to have left the band for an unknown reason.

If  you've  got the second CD, you cand find a so called secret track
at  the  end  of  this one. This track  is dedicated to the memory of 
Aaron Seth Anderson.

DOWNSET  is  a  highly  anti-sexism, anti-U.S.A. system, anti-racism, 
anti-Milli Vanilly ( Ha Ha ! You need to buy the CD  to  hear this. I
give you an indication : listen  carefully  to  the 4th  track of the
band's first album ).

I hope that you have liked this ( short ) article, maybe another  one
from me soon, with the same bad english...


                             see ya all,
                             support "Point & Rock",
                             and don't forget;
                            
                     None are more hopelessly enslaved, 
                than those who falsely believe they are free.
                            
                                              J.W. VAN GOETHE



Article written by "NEC/HEMOROIDS"
                   HURTAUX LUDOVIC
                   8 rue du danube
                   51100 Reims
                   France
         my phone: 0-326-073-123

