@Node Albums "Albums to listen"

@{b}Albums to listen@{ub}

This time, we have 4 albums in tests, a record !!! We'll give you our
opinion on the following albums :

@{"Aerosmith" Link Aerosmith} : Nine Lives
@{"Tool" Link Tool} : Aenima
@{"Marylin Manson" Link Manson} : Smells Like Children
@{"Uncle Meat" Link Meat} : Swallow

We have decided to change our quotation system. You will  now have to
deal  with   stars.  Signification   is  just  like  in  the  belgian
universities :

- [*][*][*][*][*] = Very high distinction
- [*][*][*][*][ ] = High distinction
- [*][*][*][ ][ ] = Distinction
- [*][*][ ][ ][ ] = Satisfaction
- [*][ ][ ][ ][ ] = Insufficient
- [ ][ ][ ][ ][ ] = Exclusion mark

@endnode

@Node Tool "Tool : Aenima"

@{b}Tool : Aenima@{ub}

Yes, I know this album is not recent ( and also  other albums in test
here ), but I heard in different places that Aenima was  a good piece
of work. I finaly decided to  buy  it and put my hear on these songs.

First  of  all, the  cover  is  beautiful. There  is a great artistic
research, as the music itself. Imagine numbers on  eyes following you
when you incline the CD box... Effect guaranteed !!!

But the music ??? The  first  time  you  listen  this  album, you are
shocked by  the  power  of  the composition, even if the tempo is low
sometimes. You  could  also  be  deranged  by  some strange songs ( I
recommend you "(-) Ions" ), but  as  I already told you, this is very
artistic. There is  even  a  song in German ( "Die Eier von Satan" ).
During more than 77 minutes, you will  be attacked by loud and strong
guitars and other strange instruments.

The singer sings his lyrics in  a very  melodic way. Just a shadow in
this painting, no  lyrics  are printed  on  the  cover. I  am  always
frustrated when this  happens because I can't sing the songs... Maybe
I  will  find  it on Internet ( and give it to you in a near issue ).
The singer can give some dark atmosphere at the songs, it's great.

If you  like  to discover new things, you certainly can give a chance
to this album.

My quotation : [*][*][*][*][*]

@endnode

@node Aerosmith "Aerosmith : Nine Lives"

@{b}Aerosmith : Nine Lives@{ub}

Aerosmith  is  finaly  back with their new album called "Nine Lives".
The last album was in 1993, it's quite long !

So,  how  is  it,  will  you  ask ??? I  will answer good ( if not, I
wouldn't wrote down those lines... only  good  albums  are  tested in
Point & Rock ).

Everything begins with some cats crying in your hear and "Nine Lives"
is launched. It's a great song to begin the album.

Just like Get A Grip, we  can  recognize the "Aerosmith touch". There
is  for  every  taste :  strong  songs  like  "Nine  Lives", "Crash",
"Something's Gotta Give", "Falling In Love" ( I  especialy  like  the
bass guitar on this song )... but  also  songs  that  will make girls
cry : "Fallen Angels", "Hole In My Soul",...

No  indications  about  that  but  I suspect Joe Perry to sing on one
song : put an hear on "Falling Off", you will hear  that it's another
singer or that Steven Tyler can change his voice...

There is a note of exoticism with "Taste Of India" with indian sounds
in  the  debut.  This  song  must   have  influenced  the  graphician
responsible of the cover picture ( an indian catwoman dancing amongst
serpents ).

The packaging is absolutely fabulous : on  each  page of the booklet,
there is a picture which  is  part  of the  next picture and so on...
Just one thing, NO  LYRICS  printed !!!  Grrrr... I  hate it, another
thing to search on internet ( but  I  should  be  glad,  it's another
thing to put on the mag :) ).

So, if you're a fan of Aerosmith, you can surely go and buy this CD !

My quotation : [*][*][*][*][*]

@endnode

@Node Manson "Marylin Manson : Smells Like Children"

@{b}Marylin Manson : Smells like children@{ub}

You can tell me this album was out last year, I've  listen to it some
days ago only ! Hey, nobody's perfect...

So, I was thinking that sometimes I was listening to strange piece of
music, but  this  album  swept all my thoughts !!! I have never heard
such a debauchery of crazy songs. Madness is here, it's sure.

During all the album, you can  feel  a huge unhealthy atmosphere. You
can be  sometimes  deranged by some sick passages ( just like in "May
Cause Discoloration Of Urine Or Feces" or "F*** Frankie" --- even the
titles are crazies !!! ).

But the music  is strong and  you are surprised to continue to listen
this album, just maybe to discover until where the  sir Manson can go
in his madness.

A big  surprise is the reprise of "Sweet Dreams ( are made of this )"
of Eurythmics. If  you have not seen the video clip already, you MUST
see it ! You'll see how  much this group is sick ( for our joy I must
say ). Sometimes  I  wonder  myself  if  Marylin Manson is not @{u}REALLY@{uu}
crazy !!!

It's certainly an album to listen 1 time in your life !!!

My Quotation [*][*][*][*][ ]

@endnode

@Node Meat "Uncle Meat : Swallow"

@{b}Uncle Meat : Swallow@{ub}

Internet has something good in the  fact  that  you can meet some new
friends. And sometimes, those friends are  playing in a group of Hard
Rock. That's what happened to me some weeks ago. Lestat introduced me
to a guy who was  loving  my  humble  work ( this  mag ! ). This guy,
named Afreak on IRC is  the  drummer  in a belgian band called "Uncle
Meat".

He  told  me  that  their  new  album  was out ( "Underneat" ). I was
searching for this album  and I have not found it yet. But, a CD shop
was closing  his  doors and  cutting prices with 80% off. I thought :
"I should enter and see what's yet  in  the stores". Quite nothing in
fact, but my  eyes  where  attracted  by  a  little black cover, with
strange red fishes. On the cover, just a  label  with  a name  and  a
title : Uncle Meat : Swallow !!!

The world is very small.... Well, I  have  bought  this  album ( at a
very ridiculous price ( a little more than.... 1 $ !!! ).
( Afreak,  excuse  me  for  this  price, it's a  good business for my
wallet but your music deserves more than it !!! ;-) ).

I introduced the CD in the player, and  I  went surprised by the good
sound coming from the speakers. I didn't  know  what  kind  of  music
Uncle Meat was playing, but it's Metal  and  I like Metal. Sometimes,
it makes me think to Channel Zero ( another  belgian group ), but the
voice is different, lower than the singer of this band.

The composition are well build, the guitars  are very present, and if
I have well understood, there is only 1 guitar player ( who  is  also
the singer ).

This album pleased me and I would like  to listen to the second crime
of Uncle Meat ;-) .

Just a note, it's the third CD I bought this day, and  it's the third
without the lyrics !!! @{b}IS IT A CONSPIRATION AGAINST SINGERS ????@{ub}

So, if you see  this album on  the  shelves, you can support a friend
and buy it !

You can visit their internet site and leave them a message on :

http://www.club.innet.be/~mon00372/aindex.html

My quote : [*][*][*][ ][ ]

@endnode

